1Ô∏è‚É£ Platform Onboarding Checklist (Host Platform ‚Üí BG System)

This checklist is platform-facing (what they must configure / agree to before go-live).


---

A. Commercial & Ownership Alignment

[ ] BG system identified as micro-frontend / external capability

[ ] Host platform confirmed as identity & journey owner

[ ] BG system confirmed as authorization-only (no login)



---

B. Authentication & Trust Setup

Platform ‚Üí BG Auth Service

[ ] Client credentials issued (client_id, client_secret)

[ ] Token audience (aud) agreed (e.g. bg-backend)

[ ] Token signing algorithm agreed (HS256 / RS256)

[ ] Token introspection / validation mechanism agreed


Network Trust

[ ] IP allowlist configured (if required)

[ ] Mutual TLS decision documented (optional)

[ ] TLS version ‚â• 1.2 confirmed



---

C. API Contract Finalization

Required APIs

[ ] /token (Platform OAuth)

[ ] /getVetted (Journey ‚Üí BG entry)

[ ] /submit (BG exit ‚Üí next screen)


Mandatory Fields (No Renaming Allowed)

[ ] winame

[ ] bgreferencenumber

[ ] requestId

[ ] sessionID

[ ] requestingapp

[ ] producttype = BG

[ ] subproducttype = NBG



---

D. Journey Orchestration

[ ] getVetted mapped to BG Vetting step

[ ] Submit API mapped to next journey screen

[ ] Duplicate submit handling defined (409 expected)

[ ] Cancel / timeout behavior documented



---

E. Frontend Embedding

[ ] Embedding mode confirmed (iframe / redirect)

[ ] Token never exposed via URL params

[ ] Context passed via secure payload

[ ] Cross-origin policy agreed (CORS)



---

F. Error Handling Agreement

Scenario	Expected

Token expired	Platform re-initiates getVetted
Duplicate submit	Platform blocks navigation
BG mismatch	Platform shows generic error
Host submit failure	Retry / manual fallback


[ ] Error codes mapped between systems

[ ] No internal error messages exposed to user



---

G. Audit & Compliance

[ ] BG reference included in all logs

[ ] User ID propagated (masked if needed)

[ ] Submit timestamp captured

[ ] Retention policy agreed



---

H. Pre-Go-Live Validation

[ ] End-to-end UAT completed

[ ] Token expiry tested

[ ] Replay attack tested

[ ] Multiple tabs scenario tested

[ ] Pen-test signoff (if required)



---

‚úÖ Platform Onboarding Exit Criteria

> Platform can safely launch BG vetting with zero identity duplication and full audit compliance.




